Wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Trim @mini cucumber{1}; using a #peeler{}, shave cucumber lengthwise into thin ribbons, rotating as you go, until you get to the seedy core. Discard core. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Roughly chop @peanuts{1/2%oz}.

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Salmon Cakes ==

Pat @salmon{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Using a #sharp knife{}, slowly cut between flesh and skin ½ inch at a time, being careful not to cut into flesh, until skin is fully removed from fish. Discard skin. Cut salmon into ¼-inch cubes.

> TIP: The smaller the pieces are, the better—this will help bind the ingredients together!

In a #large bowl{}, combine salmon, @Panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, @green curry paste{2%tbsp}, and half the @mayonnaise{4%tbsp}. Using your hands, firmly press together and shape salmon mixture into four equal patties (eight patties for 4 servings), each about ½ inch thick.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium heat. Add patties and cook until golden brown and cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}.

== Cucumber Cabbage Slaw ==

While salmon cakes cook, in a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, juice from half the lime, and @salt{pinch} (4 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp sugar for 4 servings).

Add cucumber ribbons, @coleslaw mix{4%oz}, and half the cilantro; toss to evenly coat.

== Sweet Chili Aioli ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz}, remaining mayonnaise, and juice from remaining lime.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in lime zest and remaining cilantro. Season with @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.

Divide rice, salmon cakes, slaw, and sweet chili aioli between plates in separate sections. Garnish slaw with chopped peanuts and serve.